{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, considering the defendant's lack of prior criminal history and the effort to make partial restitution, a maximum sentence is not warranted. A brief period of incarceration serves as a sufficient deterrent and punitive measure without severely derailing the defendant's ability to reintegrate into society and finish paying back the stolen funds.",
  "verdict": 6
}
